Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specify_pg_keepout(25.10)                            specify_pg_keepout(25.10)

Name
       specify_pg_keepout - Defines the PG keepout box for a cell or a pin

Syntax
        specify_pg_keepout

       [-help]

       [-bottom <value>]

       [-left <value>]

       [-pin <string>]

       [-right <value>]

       [-top <value>]

       {-cell  <lib_cell_name> | -inst <instance_name>} {-layer <layer_name> |
       -layerId <layer_id>}

       Defines the PG keepout box for a cell or a pin.

       PG keepouts can be applied on the cell or cell pin. Keepout values  can
       be  positive  or negative and are always from the edge for both pin and
       cell.

Parameters
       -bottom <value>
              Specifies the value to expand the  keepout  box  on  the  bottom
              side.

       -cell <lib_cell_name>
              Specifies  the  lib  cell that needs to be constrained by the PG
              keepout box.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each specify_pg_keepout parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man specify_pg_keepout

       -inst <instance_name>
              Specifies  the  instance  that needs to be constrained by the PG
              keepout box.

       -layer <layer_name>
              Specifies the layer on which the PG keepout box is applied.  The
              layer is the LEF/OA name of routing layers.

       -layerId <layer_id>
              Specifies  the layer Ids on which the PG keepout box is applied.
              The layer Id is the layer number of routing layers.

       -left <value>
              Specifies the value to expand the keepout box on the left side.

       -pin <pin_name>
              Specifies the pin that needs to be constrained by the PG keepout
              box.

       -right <value>
              Specifies the value to expand the keepout box on the right side.

       -top <value>
              Specifies the value to expand the keepout box at the top.

Example
       The following command keeps mycustomcell/the_m4_pin away from M5  power
       stripes:

       specify_pg_keepout -cell mycustomcell -pin the_m4_pin -layer M5

